rComments: She was fabulous! Honestly, I don't understand why people rate her below 5 stars. I'm not terribly amazing at chemistry but she helped so much during her office hours. I advise everyone to take advantage of that. She's very understanding and she is honestly THE BEST professor I've had here. Props to Yerkes! Review the Lon capa for the quizzes. It really helps to get those done early.

She speeds through a lot of important materials and expect it to be tested in detail later. The discussion sections are where I actiually learn the material. Usually I have no idea what she is talking about in class.

Prof Yerkes knows what she's talking about and even though she does speak fast during lectures, she is ALWAYS available for office hours to clear things up. She is pretty straightforward and is also really flexible when it comes to grading. She is also better at preparing you for organic chemistry than some of the other professors.

Yerkes is an awesome professor. She is always available for office hours and is really helpful. She posts notes, lectures, practice problems, and many other resources online, which a lot of other professors don't do. As long as you try, you should be able to do just fine.

Even though I hear a lot of people complain about Yerkes, I really didn't think she was all that bad.  This class is in no way easy but as long as you go to lecture and pay attention you should do just fine. She does fly through lecture pretty quickly so make sure to keep up. Her quizzes are easy but watch out for her exams, they are no joke.
She is not very helpful when I went to get help with problems, I felt she was condescending.

Take Decoste. Seriously. This teacher is B.S. Her curriculum is ridiculous, you have to learn 10times more then Decoste's curriculum. If your not an idiot then don't take her. Shape your schedule around so you DO NOT GET YERKES. Trust me, even if you study, unless you have a strong background in Chem your gonna get your A S $ kicked.

Not a bad professor, in my opinion.  Her lectures are streamlined and very easy to follow.  She does stress basics during lecture, but she gives plenty of opportunity to apply all the course material before exams.
She reads her slides, teaches the easy stuff, tests the hard stuff. Take Ray or whoever else teaches this class because she does everything a prof is supposed to not do.
Her exact words for our orgo Chem... "You only have to memorize 10 words to get an A" Anybody that knows orgo at all knows that is not true.

I took yerkes for both 102 and 104...no its not an easy class, but she is the easiest of the chem professors i think.If your a more math based student shes a better teacher for you.she stresses math above conceptual stuff.need help, go to her office hours, shes cool and down to earth. for chem 104 i barley went and got a B+.Not too hard of a class

She makes test questions where there is not a right answer as a choice... It happened all 3 times for our class, then she refuses to throw out the question.  She also lectures on the basics, but tests on the toughest material.
I didn't feel like she cared about teaching at all. I have a different professor this semester for 104 and it has made going to class a lot easier.

She is a decent professor. She definitely should not read straight off her powerpoints like she does, and her tests are tricky for no reason, but if you can pay attention and keep up in class, you should do fine. One thing that really helped me was getting the book of past hour exams from the bookstore. If you can nail those, you will be fine.

she good for 102 and for 104 not so much. She emphisizes orgo way too much and it doesnt give you an advantage when 232 comes around. Take her for 102 and youll do well but take Ray for 104. Its just less of a head ache.

She's very boring and reads off of her power points directly so you don't even have to go to class if you just read the power points and the book. Her exams are unnecessarily hard and most of the time she doesn't know how to answer them herself.
Make people sleep

She's a decent professor, but bored me to death.  Powerpoints are generally fine by me, but she read off of them directly.  A good professor doesn't do this.  I've had professors who read off the screen, and others who don't.  The ones who don't are general more effective professors.  And I must say, she didn't seem at all interested in what she wa
She goes way to fast on account of reading directly off of her powerpoints. I hear that her class goes more in depth and is a lot harder than the comparitive teachers and subjects
Great professor, if you are at all competent you shouldn't get less than an A.
